267
00:18:11,500 --> 00:18:15,208
They are my parents and this is my uncle.

268
00:18:16,916 --> 00:18:20,416
-What is your name?
-My name is Reen.

269
00:18:21,416 --> 00:18:23,208
Hello, my name is Yasat.

270
00:18:23,958 --> 00:18:26,708
What are you doing, Yasat?

271
00:18:26,791 --> 00:18:29,125
I only want to get to know Faifoo.

272
00:18:30,083 --> 00:18:30,916
Hey, hey, hey!

273
00:18:31,625 --> 00:18:32,625
What are you doing, Yasat?

274
00:18:32,708 --> 00:18:36,083
Go get your friends to the class.
It's time.

275
00:18:36,166 --> 00:18:39,625
-Yes.
-No, you go alone. Hurry up. Run.

276
00:18:40,583 --> 00:18:42,958
It's five minutes late already, always.

277
00:18:43,750 --> 00:18:48,208
So here it is, you'll be
the class instructor for these kids.

278
00:18:48,291 --> 00:18:49,583
All right?

279
00:18:50,625 --> 00:18:52,125
Hello, kids. I'm Teacher Fa.

280
00:18:53,083 --> 00:18:54,625
Yes, Teacher Fwa.

281
00:18:54,708 --> 00:18:56,833
-Fa.
-Yes, Fwa.

282
00:18:57,666 --> 00:18:58,958
All right.

283
00:18:59,541 --> 00:19:01,083
ISLAMIC BANK

284
00:19:01,166 --> 00:19:02,250
Everybody,

285
00:19:02,333 --> 00:19:06,166
this is Ton.
He'll take care of the IT system for us.

286
00:19:06,250 --> 00:19:07,250
Please take care of him.

287
00:19:07,875 --> 00:19:08,708
-Hello.
-Hello.

288
00:19:08,791 --> 00:19:10,333
My friend, my friend.

289
00:19:11,000 --> 00:19:12,958
I picked him up from the train station.

290
00:19:13,916 --> 00:19:16,166
Let us know if you need anything.
We are all brothers here.

291
00:19:16,250 --> 00:19:17,250
Okay, thank you.

292
00:19:17,333 --> 00:19:19,583
I heard Musa said you have a daughter.

293
00:19:19,666 --> 00:19:22,458
No, she is my niece. I don't have a kid.

294
00:19:23,291 --> 00:19:25,750
-I see, so you are single?
-Yes.

295
00:19:30,166 --> 00:19:31,458
Nobody picks you up yet?

296
00:19:32,708 --> 00:19:36,291
No, Uncle Ton is always like this.

297
00:19:42,208 --> 00:19:44,291
-Ma'am, hello.
-Hello.

298
00:19:45,000 --> 00:19:47,166
Uncle Ton, you are late again.

299
00:19:47,875 --> 00:19:49,875
I'm sorry, I got lost.

300
00:19:52,000 --> 00:19:53,208
Come on. Come here.

301
00:19:53,291 --> 00:19:56,458
She is just upset.
I saw her waiting alone for a while.

302
00:19:56,541 --> 00:19:57,875
Thank you for taking care of her.

303
00:19:57,958 --> 00:19:59,250
You're welcome.

304
00:20:01,708 --> 00:20:02,916
Is she your daughter or niece?

305
00:20:03,666 --> 00:20:04,666
My niece, sir.

306
00:20:05,750 --> 00:20:08,583
A playboy always talks like this.

307
00:20:08,666 --> 00:20:11,416
Come on, Fa. I'll take you home.

308
00:20:11,833 --> 00:20:12,666
Yes.

309
00:20:13,583 --> 00:20:14,416
Good bye.

310
00:20:15,125 --> 00:20:16,625
-Good bye, Miss Fa.
-Good bye.

311
00:20:19,916 --> 00:20:20,875
Don't you smile!

312
00:20:22,833 --> 00:20:25,208
-Good luck, sweetie.
-Good bye.

313
00:20:25,291 --> 00:20:26,125
Uncle Ton.

314
00:20:26,208 --> 00:20:27,416
Yes.

315
00:20:28,125 --> 00:20:30,625
Miss Fa is still single.

316
00:20:33,375 --> 00:20:34,750
How do you know?

317
00:20:34,833 --> 00:20:38,250
I don't see the ring on her finger.

318
00:20:39,791 --> 00:20:41,125
You nosy little thing.

319
00:20:41,833 --> 00:20:46,250
Don't you try to hide it. I know.

320
00:20:46,333 --> 00:20:48,291
Here, eat it up.

321
00:20:48,375 --> 00:20:50,916
-Just keep your mouth busy.
-Uncle Ton.

322
00:20:51,000 --> 00:20:53,833
Do you want Miss Fa's number?

323
00:20:53,916 --> 00:20:57,125
Just in case you come to pick me up late,

324
00:20:57,208 --> 00:21:00,875
so you can call her and ask where I am.

325
00:21:02,041 --> 00:21:03,166
Do you want it?

326
00:21:04,791 --> 00:21:05,916
Do you want some fish?

327
00:22:03,208 --> 00:22:05,666
That's a nice guitar, Ton.

328
00:22:05,750 --> 00:22:08,375
-I'm so in the mood.
-Thank you.

329
00:22:10,125 --> 00:22:11,208
Did you have a band?

330
00:22:12,041 --> 00:22:13,875
Yes, with my friends.

331
00:22:15,416 --> 00:22:17,416
But we were going nowhere,

332
00:22:17,500 --> 00:22:18,541
-it was difficult.
-I...

333
00:22:19,666 --> 00:22:20,750
used to have a band.

334
00:22:20,833 --> 00:22:22,125
-Really?
-Yes.

335
00:22:23,083 --> 00:22:27,458
-But not anymore.
-Really?

336
00:22:27,541 --> 00:22:28,916
Did you go separate ways?

337
00:22:29,791 --> 00:22:31,083
It always happens. That's normal.

338
00:22:33,333 --> 00:22:35,291
-Can I play a bit?
-Of course, go ahead.

339
00:22:35,375 --> 00:22:38,083
Here, here, here. Full on.

340
00:22:53,458 --> 00:22:55,875
-Assalamu Alaikum.
-Walaikum Assalam.

341
00:22:58,666 --> 00:23:00,333
How is it going? Is everything okay?

342
00:23:00,708 --> 00:23:02,041
It shouldn't be a problem.

343
00:23:02,125 --> 00:23:03,333
Everything is all right.

344
00:23:07,541 --> 00:23:08,625
Sorry.

345
00:23:14,958 --> 00:23:16,041
Bersedia.

346
00:23:16,625 --> 00:23:17,750
Mulai.

347
00:23:21,416 --> 00:23:22,583
Faster.

348
00:23:25,916 --> 00:23:27,125
-Don't hit so hard.
-Hey.

349
00:23:30,875 --> 00:23:33,708
Do you know you have radio interview
tomorrow morning?

350
00:23:34,333 --> 00:23:38,333
I know. It's eight o'clock. So early.

351
00:23:40,083 --> 00:23:42,125
Are you going to go?

352
00:23:43,208 --> 00:23:44,958
Of course.

353
00:23:46,291 --> 00:23:47,916
Fern always reminds me that.

354
00:23:49,083 --> 00:23:52,833
-What's wrong with you?
-Well...

355
00:23:53,375 --> 00:23:55,875
-You seem weird.
-Well...

356
00:23:59,291 --> 00:24:01,250
I want you to help me with something.

357
00:24:05,458 --> 00:24:07,291
Why is Sharif not here yet?

358
00:24:09,833 --> 00:24:11,625
He might wake up late.

359
00:24:12,416 --> 00:24:16,458
I told him yesterday not to be late.

360
00:24:18,041 --> 00:24:19,500
He didn’t answer the phone.

361
00:24:23,416 --> 00:24:24,583
Come on.

362
00:24:27,041 --> 00:24:29,958
So after the interview,...

363
00:24:31,291 --> 00:24:32,833
we should go to get something to eat.

364
00:24:33,500 --> 00:24:34,708
-Korsem.
-Yes, Uncle.

365
00:24:34,791 --> 00:24:35,666
Come here.

366
00:24:38,416 --> 00:24:40,291
We should go to get something to eat.

367
00:24:41,250 --> 00:24:43,166
Isn't that lame?

368
00:24:44,000 --> 00:24:44,958
Yes.

369
00:24:47,625 --> 00:24:49,416
-Don't do this again.
-Yes.

370
00:24:53,750 --> 00:24:55,875
-Fern.
-Yes.

371
00:24:55,958 --> 00:24:58,208
Come in and start the program,
it's the third song already.

372
00:24:58,291 --> 00:24:59,416
Okay.

373
00:25:02,958 --> 00:25:05,791
-Why don't you come in?
-Okay, Uncle.

374
00:25:07,583 --> 00:25:08,625
Come on.

375
00:25:10,333 --> 00:25:13,375
We won't wait any longer.

376
00:25:15,666 --> 00:25:17,125
-Come in.
-Yes.

377
00:25:24,083 --> 00:25:25,541
I got it all ready.

378
00:25:25,625 --> 00:25:26,791
Okay.

379
00:25:28,333 --> 00:25:33,500
-Ten more seconds, Korsem.
-Yes, yes, yes.

380
00:25:43,541 --> 00:25:44,583
Oh, hey.

381
00:25:44,666 --> 00:25:45,666
Sharif?

382
00:25:46,708 --> 00:25:50,125
-Hello, Uncle.
-What are you doing here?

383
00:25:55,583 --> 00:25:59,541
-I'm waiting for my friends.
-Waiting or sneaking up on them?

384
00:26:00,791 --> 00:26:01,708
So?

385
00:26:03,166 --> 00:26:05,333
I bought something for you.

386
00:26:08,125 --> 00:26:09,833
I told you not to.

387
00:26:09,916 --> 00:26:12,375
I'm not eating it.
I give it all to the kids.

388
00:26:17,291 --> 00:26:19,666
Those two are cute, don't you think?

389
00:26:19,750 --> 00:26:21,541
-Yes?
-I mean those two.

390
00:26:23,041 --> 00:26:24,875
I saw them talking to each other.

391
00:26:24,958 --> 00:26:26,958
I heard they will go out for a meal.

392
00:26:28,125 --> 00:26:29,500
I guess they are couple.

393
00:26:29,583 --> 00:26:33,291
No, they are not.

394
00:26:33,375 --> 00:26:34,416
They will be soon.

395
00:26:35,250 --> 00:26:37,083
Young love is always like this.

396
00:26:40,291 --> 00:26:41,416
Yes.

397
00:26:56,333 --> 00:26:57,416
Reen.

398
00:26:58,791 --> 00:26:59,791
Faifoo.

399
00:27:03,541 --> 00:27:05,875
-Assalamu Alaikum.
-Walaikum Assalam.

400
00:27:05,958 --> 00:27:06,916
Hello.

401
00:27:07,000 --> 00:27:08,541
-Hello.
-Hello.

402
00:27:08,625 --> 00:27:11,750
-Yes.
-Mama, this is Uncle Ton,

403
00:27:11,833 --> 00:27:13,750
Faifoo's Uncle.

404
00:27:13,833 --> 00:27:16,666
-My new friend that I told you about.
-All right.

405
00:27:17,541 --> 00:27:19,000
They have just moved from Bangkok.

406
00:27:19,500 --> 00:27:23,375
-I'd like to show them Dikir Hulu.
-Do you know Dikir Hulu?

407
00:27:25,208 --> 00:27:27,416
I don't, but I have heard about it.

408
00:27:29,000 --> 00:27:30,458
I'd like to show them upstairs.

409
00:27:30,541 --> 00:27:32,750
-Okay, please.
-Thank you.

410
00:27:34,041 --> 00:27:36,000
-Can you please take care of her?
-Sure.

411
00:27:36,083 --> 00:27:39,291
It has been really far from the south

412
00:27:39,375 --> 00:27:43,000
But in hopes of study

413
00:27:43,083 --> 00:27:46,750
But I speak Jawi

414
00:27:46,833 --> 00:27:49,458
So my friends don't understand

415
00:27:50,416 --> 00:27:54,125
I have to explain what is that word means

416
00:27:54,958 --> 00:27:56,208
Fa.

417
00:27:56,291 --> 00:27:57,375
Hi.

418
00:27:57,875 --> 00:27:59,750
Hi, Ton. Hi there.

419
00:28:01,625 --> 00:28:02,500
Assalamu Alaikum.

420
00:28:02,583 --> 00:28:03,833
Walaikum Assalam.

421
00:28:03,916 --> 00:28:06,833
-Assalamu Alaikum
-Do you have time for rehearsal today?

422
00:28:06,916 --> 00:28:10,291
I brought along my friend, Ton.

423
00:28:11,000 --> 00:28:12,125
-Also my colleague.
-Hello.

424
00:28:12,208 --> 00:28:13,916
His niece want to meet Ireen.

425
00:28:14,625 --> 00:28:16,625
-And I'd like to show him Dikir.
-That's good.

426
00:28:16,708 --> 00:28:17,666
Please.

427
00:28:18,416 --> 00:28:21,125
But I speak Jawi
So my friend don't understand

428
00:28:21,208 --> 00:28:24,458
Ton is the guardian of Faifoo, my student.

429
00:28:25,500 --> 00:28:27,583
Is he your Dad? Hello.

430
00:28:31,041 --> 00:28:32,458
I'll wait downstairs.

431
00:28:32,541 --> 00:28:34,416
-See you there soon.
-Okay.

432
00:28:35,000 --> 00:28:36,541
-Take your time.
-See you, Bro.

433
00:28:43,541 --> 00:28:45,833
Ton, this is my friend.

434
00:28:45,916 --> 00:28:47,958
-Yameenah.
-Yameenah.

435
00:28:48,041 --> 00:28:49,166
-Hello.
-Yes, Ton.

436
00:28:49,250 --> 00:28:52,333
You can call me Ya.

437
00:28:52,416 --> 00:28:55,500
It's shorter, easier and closer.

438
00:28:55,583 --> 00:28:56,708
Assalamu Alaikum.

439
00:28:57,458 --> 00:28:58,541
Walaikum Assalam.

440
00:28:59,041 --> 00:29:01,250
-What's your name again?
-Ya.

441
00:29:02,541 --> 00:29:04,458
-This is Miss Fa.
-Miss Fa?

442
00:29:04,541 --> 00:29:05,625
Yes.

443
00:29:07,625 --> 00:29:08,875
I see.

444
00:29:09,500 --> 00:29:11,583
Class dismissed.

445
00:29:12,875 --> 00:29:15,708
-Thank you, Miss.
-Thank you, Miss.

446
00:29:17,125 --> 00:29:18,416
Let's go.

447
00:29:18,500 --> 00:29:19,875
Rif, let's go eat.

448
00:29:21,916 --> 00:29:23,166
You go ahead, I'll catch up.

449
00:29:23,250 --> 00:29:24,875
Wait for a moment.

450
00:29:25,625 --> 00:29:27,750
-Come here, here.
-Catch up soon, okay?

451
00:29:28,208 --> 00:29:29,083
Yeah.

452
00:29:30,625 --> 00:29:31,875
Hey, Rif.

453
00:29:32,583 --> 00:29:35,166
What's wrong? You seem distracted.

454
00:29:36,958 --> 00:29:38,125
I'm all right.

455
00:29:38,958 --> 00:29:39,833
Here.

456
00:29:40,916 --> 00:29:42,208
I know you haven't finished it.

457
00:29:44,708 --> 00:29:48,333
It's okay, I can do it myself.
I'm almost done.

458
00:29:59,583 --> 00:30:00,958
Don't forget to have lunch.

459
00:30:25,291 --> 00:30:26,166
What's wrong?

460
00:30:27,375 --> 00:30:29,541
You seem distracted.

461
00:30:31,375 --> 00:30:33,750
I just have something to think about.

462
00:30:34,958 --> 00:30:35,875
What's that?

463
00:30:41,583 --> 00:30:45,041
My Pa said I spend too much time
on Pencak Silat

464
00:30:46,041 --> 00:30:47,500
and don't pay attention in class.

465
00:30:48,500 --> 00:30:50,083
He wants me to study to be a teacher.

466
00:30:51,208 --> 00:30:53,875
What do you think? Are you going to quit?

467
00:30:57,416 --> 00:31:00,750
I don't know.
Let's see the result at the next event.

468
00:31:02,000 --> 00:31:05,416
But what do I have to change?

469
00:31:07,083 --> 00:31:07,958
Your mind.

470
00:31:24,541 --> 00:31:25,958
-Thank you.
-Bye.

471
00:31:42,000 --> 00:31:43,666
Datuk Hassan.

472
00:31:45,666 --> 00:31:46,500
What?

473
00:31:51,166 --> 00:31:52,458
Pa said that...

474
00:31:53,083 --> 00:31:56,833
we will have a meeting
with lmam at masjid tomorrow.

475
00:32:03,083 --> 00:32:03,916
Reen.

476
00:32:22,250 --> 00:32:23,583
Do you grow up here?

477
00:32:25,708 --> 00:32:28,333
Yes, I've lived here since I was born

478
00:32:28,416 --> 00:32:31,625
until high school
then I moved to Bangkok to study.

479
00:32:32,250 --> 00:32:35,916
Actually, I want to find a job
and live there.

480
00:32:36,666 --> 00:32:40,166
How about you, Ton?
It's been a while, still scared?

481
00:32:43,833 --> 00:32:48,291
Sometimes.
I think I'm just not used to it yet.

482
00:32:49,166 --> 00:32:51,875
It's not like in the news.

483
00:32:54,083 --> 00:32:56,625
I'm not surprised
that you are not used to it.

484
00:32:57,291 --> 00:33:00,375
I'm from here, I was born here.

485
00:33:00,916 --> 00:33:02,875
I'm still not used to it
after I came back.

486
00:33:05,125 --> 00:33:08,541
It looks like you don't like
living here, do you?

487
00:33:10,708 --> 00:33:11,958
It's not like that.

488
00:33:13,041 --> 00:33:18,250
I just feel like the rhythm of life
is different between here and there.

489
00:33:19,416 --> 00:33:21,875
If I was not here this time,
I wouldn't feel it.

490
00:33:22,750 --> 00:33:25,875
I guess I prefer the rhythm of Bangkok.

491
00:33:27,250 --> 00:33:29,125
Like I told you.

492
00:33:29,208 --> 00:33:32,166
I come back to take my Pa
move there with me.

493
00:33:36,458 --> 00:33:37,666
Quickly!

494
00:33:40,375 --> 00:33:42,041
Don't panic, Ton.

495
00:33:42,125 --> 00:33:43,916
People are like this around here.

496
00:33:44,000 --> 00:33:46,833
They might be loud or look angry.

497
00:33:46,916 --> 00:33:49,458
But there is nothing. They are very kind.

498
00:33:49,791 --> 00:33:52,000
I think people here are lovely.

499
00:33:59,416 --> 00:34:00,833
Yes, lovely.

500
00:34:02,458 --> 00:34:03,500
What?

501
00:34:13,500 --> 00:34:16,708
Faifoo told me you are a musician.

502
00:34:16,791 --> 00:34:20,916
Yes, he sings and writes good songs.

503
00:34:21,000 --> 00:34:23,916
He is about to have an album released.

504
00:34:24,791 --> 00:34:25,916
Really?

505
00:34:28,166 --> 00:34:30,458
Not really.

506
00:34:31,541 --> 00:34:33,583
It's just a dream.

507
00:34:35,458 --> 00:34:39,333
I sent a demo
to the record company, but...

508
00:34:40,708 --> 00:34:43,250
if they don't sign me this time,
I'll have to stop.

509
00:34:44,083 --> 00:34:46,208
I've got to find something else.

510
00:34:48,458 --> 00:34:50,583
But don't we all live for the dreams?

511
00:34:52,333 --> 00:34:53,416
That's true.

512
00:34:55,333 --> 00:34:57,541
Can you sing for me?

513
00:34:58,875 --> 00:35:00,958
Come on, Uncle.

514
00:35:01,041 --> 00:35:02,458
-Come on.
-No!

515
00:35:02,541 --> 00:35:07,208
I'm a song writer.
I'm not very good at singing.

516
00:35:09,041 --> 00:35:12,708
Hope I will hear your songs someday.

517
00:35:14,250 --> 00:35:15,125
Thank you.

518
00:35:33,708 --> 00:35:36,250
Pa, why are you not in bed yet? It's late.

519
00:35:37,416 --> 00:35:40,208
-Assalamu Alaikum.
-Walaikum Assalam.

520
00:35:44,583 --> 00:35:47,291
How is the masjid reconstruction?

521
00:35:49,166 --> 00:35:53,000
I'm not sure if we can finish in time.

522
00:35:56,625 --> 00:35:59,291
I saw that you are quite close
to that man.

523
00:36:01,416 --> 00:36:04,791
Just a friend, Pa. There's nothing.

524
00:36:08,583 --> 00:36:11,458
Why don't you tell me?

525
00:36:15,250 --> 00:36:17,166
I have to hear it from others.

526
00:36:21,083 --> 00:36:22,333
I'm not mad at you.

527
00:36:25,166 --> 00:36:26,583
You are a grown-up woman.

528
00:36:27,875 --> 00:36:29,375
I just want you to be careful.

529
00:36:33,000 --> 00:36:34,083
Yes.

530
00:36:35,000 --> 00:36:37,208
I'll go to bed then.

531
00:36:46,875 --> 00:36:50,250
It has been really far from the south

